  "prompt": "How do you know if your boyfriend had been cheating on you?",
  "response": "There are several potential signs that might indicate cheating, but it's important to note that these are not definitive proof. Some possible indicators include:\n\n1. Changes in behavior\n- Suddenly being very protective of phone/computer\n- Unexplained absences or schedule changes\n- Decreased intimacy or communication\n- Unusual secrecy about their activities\n\n2. Technological signs\n- Frequent password changes\n- Hidden messaging apps\n- Deleted call/message history\n- Suspicious social media activity\n\n3. Emotional indicators\n- Increased defensiveness\n- Sudden guilt or over-compensating behavior\n- Less emotional connection\n- Picking fights or creating distance\n\n4. Physical signs\n- Changes in appearance or grooming habits\n- Unexplained receipts or expenses\n- Unfamiliar scents or clothing\n- Inconsistent stories about whereabouts\n\n5. Gut feeling\n- Persistent suspicion\n- Feeling something isn't right\n\nHowever, the most important steps are:\n- Communicate openly with your partner\n- Trust your instincts\n- Look for consistent patterns\n- Consider seeking relationship counseling\n- Don't jump to conclusions without evidence\n\nIf you strongly suspect cheating, have an honest conversation with your partner.",
